<p class="courseblockdesc">
Trials, hearings, grand jury; expert versus lay witness; personal and behavioral characteristics on the stand; results, reports and courtroom testimony; simulated trial testimony. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): Approval of the department.<br />
</p>
</div><div class="courseblock">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>BPS&#160;589.  Special Topics in Forensic Science.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Content may vary but will revolve around the philosophic, moral, and managerial problems associated with criminalistics practice. Topics may include evidence collection, analysis, reporting, and testimony to non-criminalistics fields. Course Information: Same as <a href="/search/?P=CLJ%20589" title="CLJ&#160;589" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CLJ 589');">CLJ&#160;589</a>. May be repeated if topics vary. Prerequisite(s): Consent of the instructor.<br />
